FBIS3-56641 "drsov012_s_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 Georgia Security Minister on Gamsakhurdia's Exhumation LD1801113094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 18 Jan 94 LD1801113094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Georgian authorities know where former Georgian President Zviad Gamsakhurdia, who committed suicide in a village in Western Georgia in the early hours of 1 January, is buried. INTERFAX reports this was stated by Igor Giorgadze, the Georgian minister of security, at a news conference in Tbilisi yesterday evening. He said that a group of specialists from Russia, Germany, and the United States was due to depart for Western Georgia today to exhume and inspect Gamsakhurdia's body. Only a visual inspection will be carried out, in keeping with what was requested by the former President's family.
